role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qnm1665702714020.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnm1665702714020.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qnm1665702714020.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qnm1665702714020\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Signature Implementation\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Signature Implementation is a Development Object that defines the technology used to implement a signature, such as Uniface, COM, SOAP and so on. A Signature can have multiple implementations. Each Signature Implementation captures the technology-specific properties of the Signature, Signature Operation, and Signature Parameters.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__section_ehb_jf1_nwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d822301e51\">Characteristics</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">impl</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ird1665702714456.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ird1665702714456.html\" title=\"A Signature is a Development Object that describes the remote interface of a component, or modeled entity operation. Signatures for Uniface components and modeled entity operations are automatically generated, but signatures for non-Uniface components that Uniface can call at runtime, must be explicitly defined.\">Signature</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Depending on the implementations, it can generate the following files:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__ul_hsl_4f1_nwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39335e1_d39336e1_d39337e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">.wsdl</span> for web services </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39338e1_d39339e1_d39340e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">.cfg</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">.dll</span> for COM components </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39341e1_d39342e1_d39343e1\">Java stub for Java components (call-in) </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39344e1_d39345e1_d39346e1\">C stub for COM components (call-in) </li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"qnm1665702714020__table_d10784e1_d10785e1_d10786e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">sig:<var class=\"keyword varname\">SignatureName</var>:impl:<var class=\"keyword varname\">Implementation</var>\n</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__section_ipv_4f1_nwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d822301e262\">Specialization</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__p_d96716e1_d96717e1_d96718e1\">Signature Implementation specializes Development Object\n        in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__ul_vwp_qf1_nwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39347e1_d39348e1_d39349e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__p_d96719e1_d96720e1_d96721e1\">It has a Signature as parent object.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39350e1_d39351e1_d39352e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__p_d96722e1_d96723e1_d96724e1\">It has no child objects and no code containers.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__li_d39353e1_d39354e1_d39355e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__p_d96725e1_d96726e1_d96727e1\">It has implementation-specific properties.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"qnm1665702714020__p_d96728e1_d96729e1_d96730e1\">It is unusual, but it is possible to have multiple\n        implementations of a signature.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615466\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615466\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Signature Implementation Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Signature Implementation A Signature Implementation is a Development Object that defines the technology used to implement a signature, such as Uniface, COM, SOAP and so on. A Signature can have multiple implementations. Each Signature Implementation captures the technology-specific properties of the Signature, Signature Operation, and Signature Parameters. Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: impl Main Development Object? No Part of: Signature Contains: Property Generalization: Development Object Specializations: — Compilation Output: Depending on the implementations, it can generate the following files: .wsdl for web services .cfg and .dll for COM components Java stub for Java components (call-in) C stub for COM components (call-in) URI format: sig: SignatureName :impl: Implementation Specialization Signature Implementation specializes Development Object in the following ways: It has a Signature as parent object. It has no child objects and no code containers. It has implementation-specific properties. It is unusual, but it is possible to have multiple implementations of a signature. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}